==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corncutter
<hw>Corn"cut`ter</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧rn"k?t`t?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A machine for cutting up stalks of corn for food of
cattle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An implement consisting of a long blade, attached to
a handle at nearly a right angle, used for cutting down the stalks of
Indian corn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corndodger</ent>⟦br⟧
